<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241450>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Dysponetus ovalisetosus n. sp.: Holotype (NMW. Z. 2012.082.0067) A. anterior end, dorsal view; B. posterior end, ventral view; Paratype (NMW. Z. 2011.039.0176) C. anterior end, ventral view; paratype (NMW. Z. 2011.039.0177) D. notochaetae; E. magnified view of notochaeta; F. neurochaetae; paratype (NMW. Z. 2011.039.0176) G. median section, ventral view—arrows indicate possible genital organs on segment 8. [d = dorsal (cirrus / cirrophore), la = lateral antenna, ma = median antenna, m = mouth appendage, p = palp, pp = pygidial projection, v = ventral (cirrus / cirrophore); segment number indicated by numerals]" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241450/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.241447>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Dysponetus bulbosus Hartmann-Schröder, 1982: unaccessioned specimen A. anterior end, dorsal view; B. notochaetal fascicle, dorsal view. [d = dorsal (cirrus / cirrophore), la = lateral antenna, m = mouth appendage, p = palp, v = ventral (cirrus / cirrophore); segment number indicated by numerals]. Images: F. Pleijel." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/241447/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

